## The Brand: E.I. Werner

### What It Is

E.I. Werner is a fantasy writer 18 years into the grind with almost nothing to show for it — and he's still going. He streams his writing live, plays games with his community, and builds his fantasy world in public.

**Brand statement:** "Writing, fantasy, and games are not escapes. They are destinations."

**Sign-off:** "When you're here, you're already there."

### What It Solves

The brand exists because he's been doing this alone for almost two decades and wants the room full of people he's never had. For fantasy lovers who've had to downplay what they love, gamers tired of apologizing for their passion, and writers in the trenches who feel alone — this is the place where you don't have to shrink.

The deepest thing the brand solves: the loneliness of loving something deeply and having no one to share it with. Evan built this because he knows what it's like to not have it.

### How It Connects to Where He Is Personally

The stream may end up being the first place where connection doesn't drain him, because the people there chose to be there for the thing he actually care about. He won't have to perform or modulate or reassure anyone. He'll just be writing. That's a different kind of not-alone than calling people back.

He is hopeful about this with clear eyes. Not manic, not hedging. He knows it's not a panacea and won't work right away. But the entire brand is designed to solve the exact isolation problem he's been living with — not just for the audience, but for himself.

### The Stream Structure

Three scheduled writing streams per week (the backbone — proves "writer who writes every day"). One scheduled gaming stream per week. The writing streams ARE the work — they don't steal time from writing, they are the writing. This is the load-bearing insight of the whole content strategy.

### Outside Inn's Role

Outside Inn is a lo-fi music and animation project that lives inside the E.I. Werner stream as the warmup and cooldown — not a separate channel, not a separate brand, not a standalone radio station. It opens every stream with lo-fi music, scrolling member names, and settling-in energy. It closes every stream as the wind-down.

This is a significant pivot from the original plan. See "The Eight Months" section for full context on how this evolved and what it cost.

### Monetization

Everything runs through Fourthwall — memberships, merch, storefront. Two membership tiers: Traveler ($7.77/month) and Innkeeper ($21.21/month). The pricing carries the base-7 DNA of the fantasy world. Revenue target: $3,000/month recurring by September 1, 2026.

Full brand strategy, content plan, and monetization structure documented separately in the EIW Brand Master Document (February 11, 2026).

