## Patterns

### 1. Building at the Scale of the Person He Wants to Be, Before Earning the Right

At SKIMS: changed his title before it was granted. Had to walk it back.

In these eight months: built a full radio station with contracted composer, hired animator, and brand identity before having a single viewer. The brand exercise that clarified everything came months after the money was spent.

The pattern isn't delusion. The things he builds are real and often good. He skips the ugly, small, unsexy version and goes straight to the version that matches his internal sense of who he is. Because the small version feels like it doesn't represent him.

**The fix:** One step before building starts. What is the cheapest, fastest way to test whether this works before I invest in making it beautiful? Build ugly first. Validate. Then make it beautiful.

He caught this pattern himself when he folded Outside Inn into the EIW stream. The goal is to catch it before the money is spent, not after.

### 2. Going Clinical Under Pressure

When stressed — financially, professionally, or relationally — he switches from warm and relational to numbered lists and clinical efficiency. This happened at SKIMS (apology emails after emotional moments, eating lunch alone, withdrawing). It happened with Carson (scope corrections email after a warm collaborative exchange). It happened because he was trained by AI advice that optimized for leverage over relationship, but he followed it because the clinical mode felt safer under financial stress.

The pattern: the warmth is there, but under pressure he leads with logic. By the time the warmth comes out, it's cleanup.

### 3. The Myths as Infinite Foundation

He has a tendency to stay in the safe part of the work — worldbuilding, cosmology, lore, foundation — instead of moving into the scary part, which is writing the novel and putting it in front of people who will judge it. The myths are genuinely massive in scope and the work is real. But "done" needs a boundary. Finish the six texts. Let the civilization document keep evolving. Then write Only Us.

### 4. Premature Self-Authorization

The title change at SKIMS. The resentment when recognition didn't come. When he starts feeling "owed," his judgment narrows.

